Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Supabase + Tailwind
第一部分：项目初始化

Prompt 1.1 — 创建项目和安装依赖
第一个运行。在终端执行，不是发给AI。
 
 PROMPT — Copy and paste into VSCode AI assistant  
You are helping me build BaysideClubs, a student organization management platform
for Bayside High School in Queens, New York.
 
Tech stack:
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- Tailwind CSS
- Deployed on Vercel
 
First, help me initialize the project. Run these commands in order:
 
npx create-next-app@latest bayside-clubs \
 --typescript \
 --tailwind \
 --eslint \
 --app \
 --src-dir \
 --import-alias "@/*"
 
cd bayside-clubs
 
npm install @supabase/supabase-js @supabase/ssr
npm install @supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs
npm install lucide-react
npm install clsx tailwind-merge
 
After installation, confirm the package.json has all these packages listed.
Then show me the exact folder structure I should have at this point.

 
Prompt 1.2 — 环境变量和Supabase配置
在Supabase官网创建项目后使用，把你的Project URL和anon key填进去。
 
 PROMPT — Copy and paste into VSCode AI assistant  
I have created a Supabase project. My credentials are:
- Project URL: [PASTE YOUR SUPABASE URL HERE]
- Anon Key: [PASTE YOUR ANON KEY HERE]
 
Please create the following files for me:
 
1. .env.local with the correct environment variables
2. .env.example (same structure but with placeholder values, safe to commit)
3. src/lib/supabase/client.ts — browser-side Supabase client
4. src/lib/supabase/server.ts — server-side Supabase client for Server Components
5. src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts — Supabase client for middleware
6. middleware.ts at root — protects authenticated routes
 
The middleware should:
- Protect these routes: /dashboard, /admin, /profile
- Allow public access to: /, /clubs, /events, /login, /register
- Redirect unauthenticated users to /login
- Refresh the session token on every request
 
Use the @supabase/ssr package for all client creation.
Use TypeScript throughout. No any types.

 
Prompt 1.3 — 数据库Schema和迁移文件
把这个提示词发给AI，让它生成所有SQL迁移文件，然后在Supabase Dashboard的SQL Editor里执行。
 
 PROMPT — Copy and paste into VSCode AI assistant  
Create the complete database schema for BaysideClubs.
Generate a single SQL file: supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql
 
Requirements:
 
-- TABLE 1: profiles (extends auth.users)
Fields: id (UUID, PK, references auth.users), email (TEXT NOT NULL),
display_name (TEXT), grade (INT, 9-12), role (TEXT, default student,
check: student|admin), avatar_url (TEXT), created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
 
-- TABLE 2: clubs
Fields: id (UUID PK gen_random_uuid), name (TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE),
slug (TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE), description (TEXT), category (TEXT,
check: Academic|Arts|Sports|Service|Tech|Other), meeting_info (TEXT),
contact_email (TEXT), cover_image_url (TEXT), is_active (BOOLEAN default true),
created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
 
-- TABLE 3: memberships
Fields: id (UUID PK), user_id (UUID ref profiles, CASCADE),
club_id (UUID ref clubs, CASCADE), role (TEXT default member,
check: member|officer|admin), joined_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
UNIQUE constraint: (user_id, club_id)
 
-- TABLE 4: events
Fields: id (UUID PK), club_id (UUID ref clubs CASCADE), title (TEXT NOT NULL),
description (TEXT), location (TEXT), starts_at (TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL),
ends_at (TIMESTAMPTZ), capacity (INT nullable = unlimited),
is_published (BOOLEAN default false), created_by (UUID ref profiles),
created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
 
-- TABLE 5: registrations
Fields: id (UUID PK), event_id (UUID ref events CASCADE),
user_id (UUID ref profiles CASCADE), status (TEXT default confirmed,
check: confirmed|cancelled), registered_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
UNIQUE constraint: (event_id, user_id)
 
-- TABLE 6: announcements
Fields: id (UUID PK), club_id (UUID ref clubs CASCADE),
title (TEXT NOT NULL), body (TEXT), created_by (UUID ref profiles),
created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
 
Also create:
1. A trigger: after INSERT on auth.users, auto-create a profiles row
2. Row Level Security policies for ALL tables:
  - profiles: users read all, users update own only
  - clubs: authenticated users read active clubs, only admin role can insert/update
  - memberships: users read own, club admin reads their club, user inserts own, club admin deletes
  - events: authenticated read published, club admin insert/update for their club
  - registrations: user reads own, event club admin reads all for event, user inserts own, user updates own
  - announcements: authenticated read, club admin insert for their club
 
Enable RLS on all tables.
Add indexes on: memberships.club_id, events.club_id, events.starts_at,
registrations.event_id, registrations.user_id

 
